
[1]ax

   AX, n. improperly written axe. [Gr.]

   An instrument usually of iron, for hewing timber and chopping wood. It
   consists of a head with an arching edge, and a helve or handle. The ax
   is of two kinds, the broad ax for hewing, and the narrow ax for
   rough-hewing and cutting. The hatchet is a small ax to be used with one
   hand.
